 Appearances (Goals). dm Pintr (born 12 June 1988 in Balassagyarmat) is a Hungarian football player who plays for Zaragoza in the Spanish first division as a defensive midfielder or a centre midfielder. He also played for the Hungarian national team. He is a polyvalent player who is able to play as a midfield player and also as a defender. His first team was MTK Budapest where he played 4 seasons, from his age of 18. Spanish club, Real Zaragoza has signed him in 2010 for 4 seasons. In his first season with Real Zaragoza he played 9 matches, for example against the Spanish giants like Real Madrid, Barcelona and Valencia. In 2011 he had an injury so that he couldn't play until December 2011. 
